  "issue_number": 164,
  "issue_title": "Add vouch stats / kb.stats for KB observability (pending queue, review rates, citation coverage)",
  "issue_body": "## What you're trying to do\n\nWhen several agents share one .vouch/ KB, I need a single read-only snapshot of how the review gate is doing: who has proposals waiting, how often proposals get approved vs rejected vs expired, and whether durable claims still have valid citations.\n\nToday that means ad hoc shell work (vouch pending --json | jq \u2026, skimming audit.log.jsonl, running vouch lint for citation problems). That\u2019s fine once, but not something I want to repeat every week or wire into CI.\n\nExample: Before a review session, I want to run one command and see that cursor-anna has 4 pending proposals (oldest ~12 days), approval rate over the last 30 days is ~70%, and 2 claims have broken citations \u2014 without parsing JSONL by hand.\n\n\n## What you've tried\n\n- vouch status \u2014 artifact counts and pending total only; no per-agent queue, ages, or review rates.\n- vouch pending / vouch pending --json \u2014 lists proposals but not aggregated by agent, ages, or historical decisions.\n- vouch audit --tail N \u2014 raw events; no approval rate or per-agent breakdown.\n- vouch lint \u2014 citation and health findings, but mixed with stale claims, dangling relations, etc.; not a focused observability summary.\n\n\n## Suggested shape\n\nAdd vouch stats and kb.stats (read-only, all transports):\n\n>vouch stats\n> vouch stats --days 30    # review window (default)\n> vouch stats --days 0     # all-time decisions\n> vouch stats --json\n> \n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-09T10:38:24.000Z",
